<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1805,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,385,1805,1830]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209">Systematic History.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[393,529,1805,1829]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Balitoropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,529,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="209">Balitoropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was created for 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith (1945)" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1945" box="[720,1003,1805,1830]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Balitoropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bartschi">
<emphasis box="[720,845,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="209">B. bartschi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[853,1003,1805,1830]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" refString="Smith, H. M. (1945) The fresh-water fishes of Siam, or Thailand. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 188, 1 - 622." type="journal article" year="1945">
Smith (
<number box="[937,995,1805,1830]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" value="1945.0">1945</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
based on having papillated lips and a deep preoral groove extending around the corners of the mouth. However, papillated lips (unculi) and a preoral groove are common characters in balitorid genera, and the genus was recognized as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,300,1909,1933]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Homaloptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,300,1909,1933]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="209">Homaloptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
van 
<bibRefCitation author="Hasselt" box="[354,500,1909,1934]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" refString="van Hasselt, J. C. (1823) Uittreksel uit een' brief van den Heer J. C. van Hasselt, aan den Heer C. J. Temminck, geschreven uit Tjecande, Residentie Bantam, den 29 sten December 1822. Algemeene Konst- en Letter-Bode voor het Jaar 1823, 2, 130 - 133." type="journal article" year="1823">
Hasselt 
<number box="[444,500,1910,1934]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" value="1823.0">1823</number>
</bibRefCitation>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kottelat" box="[542,800,1909,1934]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" refString="Kottelat, M. &amp; Chu, X. - L. (1988) The genus Homaloptera (Osteichthyes, Cypriniformes, Homalopteridae) in Yunnan, China. Cybium, 12, 103 - 106." type="journal article" year="1988">
Kottelat &amp; Chu (
<number box="[730,791,1910,1934]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" value="1988.0">1988</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1805,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209">
<taxonomicName box="[199,335,1944,1968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Balitoropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,335,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="209">Balitoropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recognized as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName box="[724,873,1944,1968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Homaloptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[724,873,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="209">Homaloptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tan" box="[918,1115,1943,1968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" refString="Tan, H. H. &amp; Ng, P. K. L. (2005) Homaloptera parclitella, a new species of torrent loach from the Malay Peninsula, with redescription of H. orthogoniata (Teleostei: Balitoridae). Ichthyological Exploration of Freshwaters, 16, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="2005">
Tan &amp; Ng (
<number box="[1049,1108,1943,1968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Randall" box="[1173,1436,1943,1968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" refString="Randall, Z. S. &amp; Page, L. M. (2012) Resurrection of the genus Homalopteroides (Teleostei: Balitoridae) with a redescription of H. modestus (Vinciguerra 1890). Zootaxa, 3586, 329 - 346." type="journal article" year="2012">
Randall &amp; Page (
<number box="[1369,1428,1944,1968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and as a genus consisting of 
<number box="[484,512,1979,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" value="10.0">10</number>
species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kottelat" box="[649,823,1978,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" refString="Kottelat, M. (2012) Conspectus cobitidum: an inventory of the loaches of the world (Teleostei: Cypriniformes: Cobitoidei). The Raffles Bullefin of Zoology, 26, 1 - 199." type="journal article" year="2012">
Kottelat (
<number box="[756,815,1979,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and of 
<number box="[914,928,1979,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" value="9.0">9</number>
species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kottelat" box="[1064,1241,1978,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" refString="Kottelat, M. (2013) The fishes of the inland waters of southeast Asia: a catalogue and core biography of the fishes known to occur in freshwaters, mangroves and estuaries. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology Supplement, 27, 1 - 663." type="journal article" year="2013">
Kottelat (
<number box="[1172,1233,1979,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" value="2013.0">2013</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Randall" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" refString="Randall, Z. S. &amp; Page, L. M. (2015) On the paraphyly of Homaloptera (Teleostei: Balitoridae) and description of a new genus of hillstream loaches from the Western Ghats of India. Zootaxa, 3926 (1), 57 - 86. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3926.1.2" type="journal article" year="2015">
Randall &amp; Page (
<number box="[159,218,2013,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" value="2015.0">2015</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recognized 
<taxonomicName box="[362,498,2013,2037]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Balitoropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[362,498,2013,2037]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="209">Balitoropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a genus consisting of 
<number box="[778,792,2014,2038]" pageId="3" pageNumber="209" value="2.0">2</number>
species based on molecular and morphological data.
</paragraph>
